    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix segfault in thread pool initialization due to missing function\n\n### Summary\nThe bounded notified FIFO implementation was missing a critical initialization function that caused segfaults when the thread pool tried to initialize worker queues. The `init_seq_ring_task` function was completely absent from the header file even though it was being called by `init_not_q`.\n\nThis manifested as null pointer dereferences and memory corruption during thread pool startup, particularly under load when multiple workers were being initialized concurrently.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/threadPool/bounded_notified_fifo.h`: Restored missing `init_seq_ring_task` function with proper atomic variable initialization.\n\nUsers may observe segfaults in `init_not_q` during thread pool creation, especially when initializing multiple worker threads. The issue becomes more pronounced under high concurrency scenarios during startup.\n"
}